Package: renalGeneticCEA
Title: Cost-Effectiveness of Renal Genetic Testing Strategies in Chronic Kidney Disease
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Zachary", "Sentell", email = "zachary.sentell@mail.mcgill.ca",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Individual-level probabilistic microsimulation model evaluating the
    cost-effectiveness of targeted gene panels, clinical exome sequencing, and a
    reflex (panel-to-exome) strategy for adults with chronic kidney disease referred
    to a specialized renal genetics clinic. Perspective: Quebec public payer (RAMQ).
    Follows CHEERS 2022 reporting guidelines.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/zacsentell/renal-genetic-testing-cea
BugReports: https://github.com/zacsentell/renal-genetic-testing-cea/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
